thousand miles away.

608
00:36:38,697 --> 00:36:40,791
Why'd I do that?

609
00:36:41,499 --> 00:36:43,525
Why did I come back?

610
00:36:46,705 --> 00:36:50,301
Why did my son have leukemia?

611
00:36:52,677 --> 00:36:55,340
I never understood any of it.

612
00:37:01,720 --> 00:37:04,053
I'm sorry for your...
For your loss.

613
00:37:09,427 --> 00:37:12,192
I... I don't really
know what to say.

614
00:37:13,832 --> 00:37:16,961
When your parents are
gone, you're an orphan.

615
00:37:17,435 --> 00:37:20,735
Spouse dies, you're
a widow, or a widower.

616
00:37:20,939 --> 00:37:23,374
But when you lose your baby...

617
00:37:26,578 --> 00:37:28,308
there's no word for that.

618
00:37:39,958 --> 00:37:42,086
See to it she gets
this before you go.

619
00:38:13,124 --> 00:38:14,615
Hey.

620
00:38:15,193 --> 00:38:18,960
Listen I... I would
really like to see you.

621
00:38:19,130 --> 00:38:22,498
I... I miss you, Elizabeth.

622
00:38:22,901 --> 00:38:27,066
Please. Please,
don't... Don't... Don't cry.

623
00:38:29,307 --> 00:38:32,368
Yeah. Tonight. Yeah.

624
00:38:32,544 --> 00:38:35,241
Yeah, I'll come over.

625
00:38:35,413 --> 00:38:37,575
I'll see you then.

626
00:38:44,589 --> 00:38:49,323
I'm sorry I wasn't there
when they came for Daryl...

627
00:38:49,894 --> 00:38:53,661
but I, uh... I had
to be somewhere.

628
00:38:57,435 --> 00:39:01,031
